POR QUE
"AMARELO"
A cor da campanha foi
adotada por conta da
trágica história que
a inspirou. Em 1994,
um jovem americano
de apenas 17 anos, chamado
Mike Emme, tirou a própria vida
dirigindo seu carro amarelo. Seus
amigos e familiares distribuíram
no funeral cartões com fitas
amarelas e mensagens de apoio
para pessoas que estivessem
enfrentando o mesmo desespero
de Mike, e a mensagem foi se
espelhando mundo afora.
Fonte: Associação Catarinense de Psiquiatria

110% ready for the holiday weekend.🪩⏳👏🏼

After the second week of the school routine, a very welcome weekend, indeed. PS: did you notice I’m not wearing shorts or anything denim, for once? Brought out this probably decade+ old missoni wrap mini skirt which paired perfectly with this thisisthegreat_ reversible bomber jacket (a gift from a styling collab showcasing their pre-fall collection). Love how the skirt’s sheen from its silk panels bring out the dusty blues from the jacket. Added the celine striped ribbed crop top for a touch of contrasting print and to add a sporty element to the blue pieces. Finished the tonal look with my morjas blue suede and leather loafers to tie the look together and add a final touch of elevated prep. 

A case of the best kind of blues…and I guess you could say I didn’t steer too far from my tried and true blue jeans look.😏

Adidas and Rave Culture

Adidas has a strong connection to rave culture, particularly in the 1990s. During this time, the brand became synonymous with the rave and music scene. Adidas tracksuits, especially the iconic three-stripe design, were highly popular as they provided comfort and unrestricted movement. In Terence Donovan's photographs capturing the Techno Scene in Birmingham, UK, and Tristan O'Neil's documentation of the House music scene in the suburbs of Milton Keynes, you can see individuals dressed in Adidas tracksuits.

The influence of Adidas in rave culture extended beyond the UK to Europe and the US. Alice Arnold's youth culture photography showcased people wearing Adidas at parties in NYC. Time Lapse Atlantis was an open party under a freeway around the Bay Area in California in which many youths that attended there were dressed in full Adidas too.

The brand is now paying homage to the various subcultures it was connected to. The cooperation from joellling in.her.room ben.c.asquith have pushed the brand towards its cultural roots with street and youth culture by reintroducing the Adimatics, Supermodifer, and Campus models as we’ve documented before. But Korn have recently announced a collaboration with Adidas which is a long-awaited partnership.

Adidas has also released a new collection called: “No Sleep Rave Club” that includes several new silhouettes, tracksuit and cap to pay tribute to the rave culture of the nineties and noughties.

dirigindo seu carro amarelo. Seus
amigos e familiares distribuíram
no funeral cartões com fitas
amarelas e mensagens de apoio
para pessoas que estivessem
enfrentando o mesmo desespero
de Mike, e a mensagem foi se
espelhando mundo afora.
